      <h1>Jobs      </h1>
      <h3>We currently have two positions available</h3>
<h3><a href="http://www.lark-it.com/jobs/#senior-system-administrator">Senior System Administrator</a> • <a href="http://www.lark-it.com/jobs/#linux-admin">Senior DevOps Engineer</a></h3>
  </section> 
      
      <h2 id="senior-system-administrator">Senior System Administrator</h2>
<h3>About Lark IT</h3>
<p>Lark Information Technology, Inc. is based in Denver, Colorado. We are a small entrepreneurial company that provides IT consulting services for mid to large-sized businesses in the Denver metro area. We are passionate about technology, and deliver high quality solutions to meet the business needs of our clients that embrace the latest technologies. We value a healthy lifestyle and work-life balance. Lark perks include a full kitchen with organic food, daily yoga and exercise classes, movie nights, and a great community of down to earth entrepreneurs. Other company benefits include flexible hours, company outings, and a focus on holistic lifestyle while still doing excellent work for our clients and ourselves.</p>
<h3>Who are we looking for?</h3>
<p>We are seeking a Senior System Administrator to join our fast-paced and highly collaborative team. This position involves working with a variety of clients performing a blend of project work, systems/end-user support and network maintenance. The diverse nature of our clients offers plenty of opportunities to keep your skills sharp and to learn new technologies.</p>
<p>You will be responsible for system updates, monitoring, troubleshooting, and providing end user support. You will also be involved with project work, which would consist of designing and deploying services into both new and existing environments. The majority of the work will be performed onsite at client offices. Remote work is done from our unique, dog-friendly, remodeled Firehouse office space south of downtown that we share with our sister company <a href="http://commercekitchen.com" target="_blank">Commerce Kitchen.</a></p>
<h3>Are you a match?</h3>
<p>The ideal candidate would have a broad technical skill set and top-notch client relationship skills. We are looking for someone who is wanting to get out from behind the desk, be on the go, engaging with our clients and solving diverse problems in multiple environments. We need someone that has consulting experience, and a passion for keeping current with the latest technology.</p>
<p>Culturally the ideal candidate would enjoy working as a team, have excellent communications skills, not be afraid to ask for help, and want to be a part of collaborative, unique, hard working team. Someone who is good at multitasking, and thrives with a bit of organized chaos would fit well in this position.</p>
<h3>Requirements</h3>
<p><strong>5+ years General Professional Experience<br />
6+ years Windows &amp; Networking Administration Experience<br />
2+ years Consulting Experience, including the following technical skills:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Experience working closely with staff and architects to understand the process of designing and implementing enterprise class solutions based on the principles of redundancy, data integrity, security and recoverability.</li>
<li>Virtualization Technologies such as VMWare ESX(i), OVirt/RHEV, etc</li>
<li>Familiarity with cloud environments</li>
<li>Experience deploying and administering Windows Server (2003-2012 )and Desktop Environments (XP – 10.0)</li>
<li>Exchange Server 2003/2007/2010/2013</li>
<li>Knowledge of Active Directory and Group Policy</li>
<li>TCP/IP, routing/subnet calculation</li>
<li>Strong Knowledge of DNS</li>
<li>Ability to pick up new skills and technologies quickly</li>
<li>Experience with pfSense, firewalls and routers, SQL / MySQL, Cisco VOIP is an advantage</li>
<li>Knowledge of Google Apps (and Google Apps Migration), or Comparable experience with similar technology (i.e., Office 365)</li>
<li>Experience with ZenDesk or other ticketing tools</li>
<li>Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, and a sense of humor</li>
<li>Flexible Schedule</li>
<li>Excellent Time Management</li>
<li>Valid Colorado Driver&#8217;s License / Automobile Insurance</li>
</ul>
<h3>What we offer</h3>
<ul>
<li>Great time off policy</li>
<li>Health benefits and 401k after 90 days</li>
<li>Ongoing training opportunities</li>
<li>Competitive pay and bonus opportunities</li>
</ul>
<h3>Apply</h3>
<p>The application process includes a phone interview, aptitude test, a very in-depth technical interview, and background checks. If we’ve kept your interest and haven’t scared you off yet, please send your resume to <a href="mailto:jobs@lark-it.com?Subject=Job%20Posting"> Jobs@lark-it.com</a> We look forward to hearing from you!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id="linux-admin">Senior DevOps Engineer</h2>
<h3>Description</h3>
<p>A mix of systems maintenance and project based work across multiple environments, each with unique requirements. Systems maintenance would include updates, monitoring, troubleshooting problems and supporting developers or other employees. Project work includes designing and deploying new services into existing and new environments.</p>
<h3>Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>Excellent interpersonal and communication skills</li>
<li>Flexible Schedule</li>
<li>Excellent Time Management</li>
<li>Ability to pick up new skills and technologies quickly</li>
<li>Work closely with customer and architects in designing enterprise class solutions based on the principles of redundancy, data integrity, security and recoverability</li>
<li>Virtualization Technologies such as VMWare ESX(i), OVirt/RHEV, etc</li>
<li>Experience with cloud environments (Rackspace, AWS, Digital Ocean, etc.)</li>
<li>Experience deploying secure Internet facing servers and applications</li>
<li>Passion for Open Source solutions</li>
<li>CentOS 5-7 deployment, configuration and management</li>
<li>Enterprise experience with Puppet and Foreman</li>
<li>Strong TCP/IP, routing/subnetting skills</li>
<li>Strong knowledge of DNS</li>
<li>Strong knowledge of HTTPS/SSL</li>
<li>Linux/Unix command line / BASH skills</li>
<li>Apache / PHP / MySQL</li>
</ul>
<h3>Preferred Skills</h3>
<ul>
<li>PCI/DSS Implementation / Auditing</li>
<li>pfSense</li>
<li>Firewall, router, switch (routing and switching)</li>
<li>Windows Server/Desktop Management (limited)</li>
<li>Nagios, Cacti, Rancid, MRTG, New Relic</li>
<li>Spacewalk / IPA</li>
<li>Katello / Vagrant</li>
<li>Scripting/Coding in bash/perl/etc to automate common tasks</li>
<li>DevOps methodologies</li>
<li>Ruby on RAILS / Capistrano / Passenger / Nginx</li>
<li>Docker</li>
</ul>
<h3>Apply</h3>
<p>Please send your resume to <a href="mailto:jobs@lark-it.com?Subject=Job%20Posting">Jobs@lark-it.com</a> We look forward to hearing from you!</p>
